ɛr is the dielectric constant of the composite;
A is the surface area of the samples in mm2 and
s is the thickness of the composite sample in mm2.
(2)G=σAs where G is the conductance of the composite in Sm−1; and A and s are the same as above. (3)σ=ωɛ0ɛ″ where ω is the frequency in the range of 10 to 100 kHz,8 and the loss tangent9 is defined as (4)tanδ=ɛ″ɛ'
